          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@gmail.com",
          "date": "2012-07-02 13:33:16.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-549 llite: Improve statfs performance if selinux is disabled",
        "message": "LU-549 llite: Improve statfs performance if selinux is disabled\n\nEven if selinux is disabled, client still tries to get selinux\nattributes from MDS. As xattrs are not yet cached, this significantly\nslows down xattr heavy operations like ls -l. This patch forces\nto return -EOPNOTSUPP on the client side if selinux is disabled.\nIt speeds up ls -l 25% for cold-cache case and 50 %for hot-cache\ncase.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nSigned-off-by: Yevheniy Demchenko <zheka@uvt.cz>\nChange-Id: I9c52ce820b4d3c3d518673cb35e1c23acefb3d8d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_2"
    }
